‚≠ê 5. CI ‚Äì Continuous Integration
‚≠ê What it means

Whenever code is added

System checks everything automatically

Finds errors early

‚≠ê Pizza example

Add topping to pizza

Check dough

Check oven

Taste test

Approve or reject

‚≠ê Code example

You run git push

CI runs tests

Checks code quality

Builds the app

‚≠ê Result

Fail ‚ùå ‚Üí Fix code

Pass ‚úÖ ‚Üí Ready for delivery

‚≠ê 6. CD ‚Äì Continuous Delivery / Deployment
‚≠ê What it means

Code is sent to users automatically

No manual upload

‚≠ê Pizza example

Pizza passed quality check

Packed automatically

Delivered to customer

‚≠ê Code example

CI passes

App deploys to server

Users see new changes

‚≠ê 7. Continuous Delivery vs Deployment
‚≠ê Continuous Delivery

Code is ready

Developer clicks deploy

‚≠ê Continuous Deployment

Code deploys automatically

No human action

‚≠ê 8. Full CI/CD flow

